race.comment: FAERIE (6) was well fancied on debut but didn't deliver, however her recent jump-outs suggest she's returned in terrific order. From a strong yard, drawn ideally, and looks the one they'll need to beat. BAS RELIEF (10) debuts for the McEvoy team off a Flemington jump-out win. The son of Brazen Beau is well drawn and profiles as a serious threat on debut. DISTINCTLY SUMMER (5) showed speed before tiring first-up. Strips fitter and is an each-way hope. SCUSIES (12) was plain fresh but is capable of sharp improvement second-up. Keep safe along with WAYNE'S DREAM (9) who will strip fitter second-up.
